President Cyril Ramaphosa has applauded the media for its role in informing the public about COVID-19. He was speaking during an engagement with South African National Editor's Forum (Sanef). JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has applauded the media for their pivotal role in informing the public about COVID-19. He was speaking during an engagement with South African National Editor's Forum (Sanef) on Sunday. COVID-19: Ramaphosa saddened by eNCA cameraman Lungile Tom's death "Through the media's reporting on the disease, you have really helped to inform and empower the people of our country but you have also stimulated public debate. Much more importantly you have helped to promote accountability and to hold those of us who are in position of power to account," he said.  There are 1,727 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa. This bring the total number of positive coronavirus cases to 30,967. There are now 32 more COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the total number to 643. According to the Health Department, a total of 701,883 tests have been conducted cumulatively of which 21,708 tests have been conducted since the last report. More than 16,116 people have recovered, resulting in more than 52-percent recovery. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.